The article discusses the negative impact of the current tax code on American consumers, companies, and workers. The author, Senator David Perdue, highlights the high corporate tax rates in the US compared to other developed countries, as well as the double tax on repatriated earnings, which has led to over $2.6 trillion in US profits being kept overseas. He argues that these factors have hindered domestic growth and made American corporations less competitive globally. Perdue also mentions the loss of American companies in the global acquisitions market due to the high corporate tax rate. He emphasizes the need to reduce the tax burden on businesses in order to create jobs, increase wages, and boost the economy. The article concludes by stating that changing the tax code by Christmas is crucial for igniting economic growth and ensuring the competitiveness of American workers.